  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0d9f\u0dba \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dcf \u0d9a\u0dd0\u0dbd\u0dd1 \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dc5\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db8\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Due to lack of fuel, forests are deserted",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "With restrictions on fueling wildlife and security forces, Polonnaruwa's various smugglers are venturing into parks and reserves.",
        "So far, timber smugglers have caused severe environmental damage by cutting down large trees in national parks including Polonnaruwa Somavathia, Maduruoya, Jalgalim Valley National Park, Trikonamaduwa, Wasgamuwa. Animal poaching has also increased there, and wildlife officials state that they do not have enough fuel to carry out raids.",
        "The drivers of the Wildlife Offices state that although a Wildlife Officer's office requested 350 liters of diesel per week, they are currently receiving 250 liters of diesel, which has also been reduced.",
        "The wildlife officers of Polonnaruwa district say that wood smugglers, hunters, treasure hunters, soil and sand smugglers are successfully carrying out their smuggling these days, and despite receiving complaints about it, they do not have enough diesel to carry out the raid.",
        "Currently, it is reported that the smugglers are successfully smuggling sand from the riverbanks in Welikanda, Vadamune, Zone 503, Maduruoya, areas and other surrounding areas and are also carrying out smuggling of kumbuk trees.",
        "Wildlife officials also state that the lives of animals in the parks and reserves of Polonnaru district are at risk due to lack of sufficient fuel."
      ],
